I know this is pittfully lacking advice, but Debbie, find a marriage therapist that is knowledgeable in PTSD, Child Sexual Abuse Survivors, and Viet Nam Vets. Yes, they are out there, but you have to shop around. Get out the yellow pages and start calling. Look under Psychologists, Clinical Social Workers, or Marriage and Family Therapists.  If they won't talk to you for free on the phone for 15 minutes, fuck em.<br>
Out line it just like I just did.  If they hesistate, fuck em.  If they are over eager, fuck em.  You want someone with at least 10 years of licensed experience.  They/we are out there, I was, but now I am burned out, so not taking any new folks on.  Others are.  You certainly can e mail me and if I know anyone in your area, I'll let you know.<br><br>
Remember one and all. Therapists and shrinks are a consumer item, just like a toaster or a set of tires.  Ask questions, read Consumer Reports, (or this site), and shop around, let me repeat that, SHOP AROUND. Don't settle for the burned out bullshitter your health plan provides. You probably will have to go out side of Cigna-Kaiser-etc to get quality instead of average.  SHOP AROUND. I can't tell you that enough. SHOP AROUND.  Form your own group of wives who have vet husbands.  Work with the nearest V.A. Hospital, they have PTSD groups and counselors, do they have services for spouses, if not, PUSH for it.<br><br>
Debbie, hope this helps. Pam, same for you. Contact me off line via e mail for any help I can give.<br><br>
